originContent: # RISC-V Vector benchmark
translatedContent: # RISC-V Vector benchmark

originContent: A collection of RISC-V Vector (RVV) benchmarks to help developers write portably performant RVV code.
translatedContent: A collection of RISC-V Vector (RVV) benchmarks to help developers write portably performant RVV code.

originContent: Benchmark results can be found at: https://camel-cdr.github.io/rvv-bench-results
translatedContent: Benchmark results can be found at: https://camel-cdr.github.io/rvv-bench-results

originContent: ## Benchmarks ([./bench/](./bench/))
translatedContent: ## Benchmarks ([./bench/](./bench/))

originContent: Contains a bunch of benchmark of different implementations of certain algorithms.
translatedContent: Contains a bunch of benchmark of different implementations of certain algorithms.

originContent: ## Instruction cycle count ([./instructions/](./instructions/))
translatedContent: ## Instruction cycle count ([./instructions/](./instructions/))

originContent: Measures the cycle count of RVV instructions by unrolling and looping over the given instruction repeatedly.
translatedContent: Measures the cycle count of RVV instructions by unrolling and looping over the given instruction repeatedly.

originContent: ## Getting started
translatedContent: ## Getting started

originContent: Start by configuring [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk), such that `make` works and optionally [./run.sh](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./run.sh), which allows you to compile and run using `make run`.
translatedContent: Start by configuring [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk), such that `make` works and optionally [./run.sh](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./run.sh), which allows you to compile and run using `make run`.

originContent: The default configuration should work with all recent clang builds and doesn't require a full cross compilation toolchain, because it builds in freestanding mode.
translatedContent: The default configuration should work with all recent clang builds and doesn't require a full cross compilation toolchain, because it builds in freestanding mode.

originContent: This means it will only work on linux, or linux syscall compatible OS.
translatedContent: This means it will only work on linux, or linux syscall compatible OS.

originContent: On recent linux versions, the performance counters aren't exposed by default, you may have to execute `echo 2 >/proc/sys/kernel/perf_user_access` and append `-DUSE_PERF_EVENT` to the `CFLAGS=...` line in [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk) (if that doesn't work, try `-DUSE_PERF_EVENT_SLOW` instead).
translatedContent: On recent linux versions, the performance counters aren't exposed by default, you may have to execute `echo 2 >/proc/sys/kernel/perf_user_access` and append `-DUSE_PERF_EVENT` to the `CFLAGS=...` line in [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk) (if that doesn't work, try `-DUSE_PERF_EVENT_SLOW` instead).

originContent: You can configure [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk) to build a hosted build or configure it with your custom toolchain, add the `-DCUSTOM_HOST` define, and implement the unimplemented functions under `#ifdef CUSTOM_HOST` in [./nolibc.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./nolibc.h).
translatedContent: You can configure [./config.mk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./config.mk) to build a hosted build or configure it with your custom toolchain, add the `-DCUSTOM_HOST` define, and implement the unimplemented functions under `#ifdef CUSTOM_HOST` in [./nolibc.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./nolibc.h).

originContent: XTheadVector isn't supported anymore.
translatedContent: XTheadVector isn't supported anymore.

originContent: ### Running benchmarks ([./bench/](./bench/))
translatedContent: ### Running benchmarks ([./bench/](./bench/))

originContent: To run the benchmarks, first look through ([./bench/config.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./bench/config.h)) and adjust it to your processor (e.g. set `HAS_E64`). If it takes too long to execute, try lowering `MAX_MEM`, which is used to scale the benchmark, and play around with the other constants until it executes in a reasonable amount of time and gives a relatively smooth graph.
translatedContent: To run the benchmarks, first look through ([./bench/config.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/./bench/config.h)) and adjust it to your processor (e.g. set `HAS_E64`). If it takes too long to execute, try lowering `MAX_MEM`, which is used to scale the benchmark, and play around with the other constants until it executes in a reasonable amount of time and gives a relatively smooth graph.

originContent: Now you can just run the benchmarks using `make run` in the ([./bench/](./bench/)) directory, or `make` to just build the executables.
translatedContent: Now you can just run the benchmarks using `make run` in the ([./bench/](./bench/)) directory, or `make` to just build the executables.

originContent: ### Measuring cycle count ([./instructions/](./instructions/))
translatedContent: ### Measuring cycle count ([./instructions/](./instructions/))

originContent: To run the cycle count measurement, first configure [instructions/rvv/config.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/instructions/rvv/config.h) to your processor.
translatedContent: To run the cycle count measurement, first configure [instructions/rvv/config.h](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camel-cdr/rvv-bench/main/instructions/rvv/config.h) to your processor.

originContent: Now you can run the measurement using `make run` in the ([./instructions/rvv/](./instructions/rvv/)) directory, or `make` to just build the executables.
translatedContent: Now you can run the measurement using `make run` in the ([./instructions/rvv/](./instructions/rvv/)) directory, or `make` to just build the executables.

originContent: For XTheadVector use the ([./instructions/xtheadvector/](./instructions/xtheadvector/)) directory instead. (this isn't maintained anymore)
translatedContent: For XTheadVector use the ([./instructions/xtheadvector/](./instructions/xtheadvector/)) directory instead. (this isn't maintained anymore)
